Text.Value: I had hoped the stones would have ensured our victory by now, but it was not to be. Let us press on - this is not over while we still draw breath.

Text.Value: I know we can. Think of all that we've already survived. Our foes should quake to see us approach them.
With the end upon us? So long as I am surviving, and I have you by my side, I am faring as well as anyone can be.

Text.Value: The sight is unnatural, but I can look past the form, to the spirit within. You did this for all of us - I am indebted, not repulsed.
We shall triumph. Our time together does not end here.
How are you faring?
How are you faring?
